Former Christie’s Chairman Tennant Dies at Age 80, Guardian Says

-- B y   C o l i n   K e a t i n g e
-- 
2011-08-13T08:31:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-13/former-christie-s-chairman-tennant-dies-at-age-80-guardian-says.html
     Aug. 13 (Bloomberg) --Anthony Tennant, a former chairman
of Christie’s International who was indicted by a federal grand
jury in  Manhattan  for allegedly fixing commission rates charged
to sellers of fine art at auction, has died at the age of 80,
the Guardian reported.  Tennant insisted from the start that he was innocent of any
wrongdoing, the newspaper said, adding that he left and never
returned to the U.S.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  